Vitality UK
September 16 at 9:59 AM ·
We are delighted to announce that Vitality is the new sponsor of the Women’s FA Cup! ⚽🏆
Our partnership with the Women’s FA Cup will run for three years through to July 2023, and will see the world’s best cup competition rebranded and referred to as The Vitality Women’s FA Cup.
Working with The FA, Vitality will drive visibility of women’s football and help to inspire more girls and women to take up football or other sports and stay active, in line with our core purpose, to make people healthier and to enhance and protect their lives.
Stay tuned for another very exciting announcement from us later today!

👇 Team news is in for tonight's Carabao Cup tie with Portsmouth Football Club at the Amex.
📲 snickersuk.com

💙 Everyone at the club was deeply saddened to hear of the passing of Albion fan Josh Bray.
Josh was one of our Christmas Wishes with this very special training ground tour back in February thanks to Bobby Zamora.
Our thoughts are with all of his loved ones.
In his memory his family have set up a fund to raise money for a stair lift to be installed in the Teenage and Young Adult unit at the Royal Marsden Hospital in Sutton.
You can donate via the link below.
https://www.justgiving.com/crowdfunding/joshybstairlift?utm_term=PrNKyaxaj.

👌 No mistake from the spot from Tomer Hemed on this day in 2016!
⚽️ Brighton Harbour Hotel ⚽️
👇 The boss previews tomorrow night's cup tie at the Amex!

💙 Here’s a look at what we’ve been doing since lockdown.
🙌 For our staff, players and supporters - together.

🙌 Head coach Graham Potter has given a positive update on the fitness of Adam Lallana and Ben White.
The pair were substituted on Monday during the 3-1 defeat to Chelsea but Potter is optimistic that both will be available for Sunday's next Premier League game against Newcastle United at St James's Park, although neither will be involved on Thursday, when the Seagulls take on Portsmouth at the Amex in the Carabao Cup.
💬 "They have both responded really well so that's good news.
"Adam took a few heavy contacts but it's not as bad as we thought. It's not muscular which is good news and we're hoping he will be training again at the end of the week.
"Ben has also responded really well and is making good progress and we're aiming to have him training as well at the end of the week. So it's positive news."

😁 Albion are pleased to announce that local fresh food wholesaler Sun Harvest have renewed their sponsorship with the club for the new season!
Albion’s Head of Commercial Russell Wood said, “Sun Harvest have been a fantastic local business to work alongside for some time now, and on behalf of everyone at the club we would like to thank them for renewing their lounge sponsorship.
“It is obviously tough times for everyone, so to see Sun Harvest commit to not only their continued sponsorship and support of the club, but the local area as well, their actions have to be commended.”
East Stand lounge sponsors and Brighton-based business Sun Harvest made over 5000 essential home deliveries during lockdown – and due to the positive response from the Sussex community they are pleased to announce that they will be continuing to offer home deliveries within Sussex!
🇪🇸 The little magician was at his best the last time we hosted Thursday night's opponents Portsmouth Football Club at the Amex! 👌

😁 If you have an announcement and would like to see it published in the Albion matchday programme for the game with Manchester United, please email your words to programme.request@bhafc.co.uk - you must attach a pic!
We are currently taking requests, on a first come, first served basis!

😁 Albion are delighted to announce that longstanding partner snickersuk.com will become the official sleeve sponsor for the men’s first team for the 2020/21 season.

It is set to be seen for the first time when Chelsea visit the Amex Stadium in the Premier League on Monday 14th September.
💬 Albion’s Head of Commercial Russell Wood said, ‘’SnickersUK.com are loyal sponsors and supporters of the club.
"We’ve been delighted to help support the expediential growth of their business which has seen their support grow from a local sponsorship to a global partnership and now they are a top-tier partner.
“You certainly cannot miss SnickersUK.com if you are an Albion fan.’’

😁 How much did that strike on the final day mean, Aaron?
🔥 Muzza's 🔝 ten for the Albion... 👇

✍️ Shane Duffy has completed a season-long loan to Celtic FC.
The Irish international heads to Glasgow after four years with Albion, following his move from Blackburn Rovers in 2016.
He moves to Parkhead with the aim of helping Celtic secure an unprecedented tenth successive league title.
Head coach Graham Potter said, “Shane is part of Albion history. He has been a big part of the club’s recent progress in winning promotion to the Premier League and in retaining our place in the top-flight.
“He is keen to play regularly and, with increased competition in the centre of defence, we cannot guarantee that. This move is a huge opportunity for Shane and on behalf of everyone at the club we wish him well for the season.
“From a personal point of view he has been an absolute pleasure to work with, and as a man and a character he is someone we all love.
“This has been a challenging year for him on and, more importantly, off the pitch, but I’m grateful for the opportunity I’ve had to work with Shane and develop the relationship I have with him.”

👊 Best of luck for the season ahead, Muzza!

text:
😍 "This is my home."
🎥 Hear from Ben White after he signed his new deal today!

😍 Ben White has extended his stay with Albion, after agreeing a new four-year contract with the club, running to June 2024.
The 22-year-old defender will be part of Graham Potter’s Premier League squad for the coming season, after an impressive season on loan at Leeds United in the Championship.
💬 Head coach Potter said, “I have been looking forward to working with Ben for a long time. He was a player I was well aware of, even before I came to the club.
“He has gradually stepped up the EFL divisions, with Newport County, Peterborough United and Leeds United.
“He had a brilliant season helping Leeds to the title last season, and now he has the opportunity to show his qualities in the Premier League.
“We are delighted to have agreed a new long-term contract with him, and I am sure our supporters will be looking forward to watching him play for the club."

✍️ Highly-rated Manchester United youngster James Garner will spend the 2020/21 campaign with Watford after agreeing a season-long loan.
The sought-after 19-year-old midfielder started three times in the Europa League last season and has made seven first-team appearances since his Premier League debut in February 2019.
In addition, Garner was named Manchester United’s Under-23 Player of the Year last term, scoring eight goals in 10 Premier League 2 games and captaining the team for much of the season.
Capable of playing in either a deep or advanced midfield role, Garner is a creative and influential operator with an excellent passing range.
He skippered England’s Under-17s during the 2018 European Championships, reaching the semi-final stage, and also played five times for his country’s Under-19 side last season.
Garner will wear squad number 16 and is available for selection as the Hornets visit Sheffield Wednesday tomorrow (Saturday September 19).
